1
00:00:05,289 --> 00:00:09,979
That fortunate soul’s wondering
the length and breadth of the brahmāṇḍa,

2
00:00:09,979 --> 00:00:14,729
means the world of misconception
and all its variagatedness;

3
00:00:14,899 --> 00:00:17,029
[Seed of Reality]

4
00:00:17,029 --> 00:00:19,836
from the Indra—
the king of Heaven,
 

5
00:00:19,836 --> 00:00:24,256
to the indra-gopa germ
on a bacterial level, 
 

6
00:00:24,256 --> 00:00:25,827
have all the possibilities.

7
00:00:25,827 --> 00:00:30,047
We’re saying, 
“A fortunate soul

8
00:00:30,047 --> 00:00:33,877
get some connection 
with Divinity, with Kṛṣṇa

9
00:00:33,877 --> 00:00:36,208
through His agent—
Guru.

10
00:00:36,738 --> 00:00:38,198
He [Śrīla Sanātana Gosvāmī]
 

11
00:00:38,198 --> 00:00:43,368
mentions in the Hari-bhakti-vilāsa
about seed, quality of seed.

12
00:00:43,368 --> 00:00:46,677
We’re saying:
bhakti-latā-bīja—

13
00:00:46,677 --> 00:00:51,887
means the seed conception,
seed Kṛṣṇa conception. 
 

14
00:00:51,887 --> 00:00:53,257
As Guru Mahārāj included

15
00:00:53,257 --> 00:00:55,506
in the Śrīla Gurudev’s
praṇāma mantra:

16
00:00:55,506 --> 00:01:00,364
Kṛṣṇa prema bija pradan—
giving the seed of affection,

17
00:01:00,364 --> 00:01:03,009
love and affection
for Kṛṣṇa.
 

18
00:01:03,009 --> 00:01:07,400
But then there is quality
and gradation everywhere,

19
00:01:07,400 --> 00:01:09,820
quality of seed.

20
00:01:09,820 --> 00:01:13,447
So Guru Mahārāj quoting
Hari-bhakti-vilāsa saying,

21
00:01:13,447 --> 00:01:16,389
“If superior quality of seed
is available
 

22
00:01:16,389 --> 00:01:20,849
no inferior seed 
should be planted.”

23
00:01:22,149 --> 00:01:23,909
That’s the consideration.

24
00:01:23,909 --> 00:01:26,775
When he was told someone
who had been apparently

25
00:01:26,775 --> 00:01:30,925
in connection with Kṛṣṇa consciousness 
for many years

26
00:01:30,925 --> 00:01:33,897
resumed their position 
in a mundane world,

27
00:01:33,897 --> 00:01:36,377
even in the position 
of an atheist,

28
00:01:36,377 --> 00:01:40,777
he said, “If the quality of seed 
is very high

29
00:01:40,779 --> 00:01:46,069
and it was planted very deeply,
that’s not possible.”

30
00:01:47,390 --> 00:01:52,982
Or will take it …
at least it will reassert.

31
00:01:52,982 --> 00:01:59,622
There is a question dormancy,
suspended animation; 
 

32
00:01:59,622 --> 00:02:00,853
many things to consider.

33
00:02:00,853 --> 00:02:05,427
As we consider 
many things in this world.

34
00:02:08,907 --> 00:02:11,907
Like cancer,

35
00:02:13,577 --> 00:02:16,502
this example can work 
in both directions.
 

36
00:02:16,502 --> 00:02:17,872
The doctors say, 
 

37
00:02:17,872 --> 00:02:19,782
“We believe
we’ve removed it all.

38
00:02:19,782 --> 00:02:21,307
Then they find out 
sometime later:

39
00:02:21,307 --> 00:02:24,732
“Oh, no, it reasserted itself.”
Something was still there—

40
00:02:24,732 --> 00:02:29,543
it’s such a powerful thing,
it’s reasserting itself again.

41
00:02:29,543 --> 00:02:34,746
It’s got recidivism.
That’s in a negative sense,

42
00:02:34,746 --> 00:02:37,082
it can also be understood
in a positive sense.

43
00:02:37,082 --> 00:02:40,868
If the seed, the quality of seed 
is very high, deep,

44
00:02:40,868 --> 00:02:46,455
profound connection with reality, 
then even if circumstantially

45
00:02:46,455 --> 00:02:51,130
it enters the suppress position,
or to the extent

46
00:02:51,130 --> 00:02:57,007
of by what is normally observable.
It can’t be seen, it’s no longer visible.

47
00:02:57,007 --> 00:03:00,878
Still it may reassert itself
in time.

48
00:03:00,878 --> 00:03:06,450
nitya-siddha kṛṣṇa-prema ‘sādhya’ kabhu naya
 

49
00:03:08,270 --> 00:03:12,870
śravaṇādi-śuddha-citte karaye udaya
[Cc: 2.22.107]

50
00:03:12,870 --> 00:03:17,640
These activities … hearing, particularly
hearing from an agent of reality,

51
00:03:17,640 --> 00:03:25,340
awakens kṛṣṇa‒bhakti in the heart.
Means it’s there in a sense

52
00:03:25,340 --> 00:03:28,699
in a dormant position, 
awakened by superior association.

53
00:03:28,699 --> 00:03:33,269
bhaktyā sañjātayā bhaktyā
[Cc: 2.25.140]

